    <note>Song(2) Qiqiu [3789] Initially served Yang(2) Xingmi's [4044] kingdom of Wu as a chief minister in 930-37 and then became the first chief minister (zaixiang) in 937-943 of the Southern Tang and again in 946-7 and in 958 (in the 12th month of this year, he was dismissed and killed himself). Wan Sitong, WuJiang dachen nianbiao, p. 4. Wan Sitong, NanTang JiangXiang dachen nienbiao, pp. 1, 2. See documentation for kin, Yue [3814] and Ci [33118] for documentation for probable ancestry and the history of this lineage.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:936:  Apt. zaixiang, first year of the Southern Tang943:  Out of office as Southern Tang zaixiang946:  Re-apt. Southern Tang zaixiang947:  Out as Southern Tang zaixiang to be Zhennan jiedu shi 《唐代人物知識ベース》記其生卒年為：887 - 959.</note>
